rComments: The only use of the projector was googling a picture of Nietzsche and showing it while he reads his 10 pages of notes. Would rather cut my right foot off and eat it raw than taking another course with him. Grading is completely random. He managed to make boring three of the most exciting thinkers ever, who do I ask for my time and money back?

Yes, the course is not an easy A and he's pretty critical when it comes to grading, but he's pleasant, helpful, and generous with his time if you approach him for clarification during or outside of class. You'll definitely enjoy having him if you're interested in the subject matter and are willing to do the work.

Not only is he an awkward and rather scatter-brained professor, but there's also little to no idea of what he wants in terms of assignments/participation. Was one of the few people who participated in discussions each weak yet still got mediocre grade for participation. Seems to mark based on his own interests/preferences, especially topic-wise.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Easily the worst lecturer I have had yet at U of T.  His lectures lack any structure or clarity, and he almost always mumbles his way through them,  so it is nearly impossible to understand him or to take down decent lecture notes. 310- I would not take ger175 again, nor would I recommend it to anyone I know.

It it very difficult to understand what he is saying and next to impossible to take notes, because he cannot formulate a thought clearly. If asked a question, he tries to answer it and goes on and on without it getting any clearer. I thought it was just me, but talked to other students after the lecture and everybody was of the same opinion

While I'm sure he knew what he was talking about I certainly didn't. He was impossible to understand, which would have been fine if he had posted notes or guidelines for what we were to understand but he didn't claiming that it dropped attendance in previous classes. Without the T.A.'s this course would've been one leap of faith after another.

I didn't understand a single word coming out of his mouth.  Many parts of his lectures had nothing to do with the material and were unimportant for succeeding in the course. If you ever have him, there is no need to go to any lectures. Just do the readings and research the topics for yourself. You'll have a better understanding that way.

Worst professor I've ever seen. His lectures are incomprehensible, monotone and completely uninspired. I walked out of class and dropped the course after 2 lectures. He stands at the front of the class and flatly reads his notes directly from the sheet for 3 hrs, doesn't post any notes online.
